   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Merryland School</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Merryland High School Limited (Merryland or the School) is a secondary education provider operating from two campuses in Entebbe, Uganda. In 2012, Merryland embarked on an expansion program to i) increase capacity at its original campus by 900 students and ii) expand to a second campus with a capacity of 1,500 students. This project began in 2012 and is partially complete. Completion is expected by the end of 2016.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">i) Increased access to affordable, quality education; ii) promoting the integration of academic and vocational education in the East African education sector; ii) demonstration of the commercial viability of quality private education in Uganda at a price point which is accessible to the middle class; iii) enhanced ability of students to earn livelihoods, both through formal employment or small scale entrepreneurship, due to vocational training.</narrative>
  </description>
